This is such a pure, sweet moment. I‚Äôm glad you shared. This quarantine has been such an emotional rollercoaster. I got laid off, am in a foreign country far from home, and I‚Äôm watching my money slowly dwindle away. It‚Äôs really scary, but I find the small moments in my life right now really touch me. Things like remembering that I had this little book of connect the dot puzzles my sister had given me years ago, or a little cross stitched picture of Yoda with the quote ‚ÄúDo or do not, there is no try.‚Äù It‚Äôs honestly the little moments that touch me the most right now, and I find myself so overcome with emotions some days. 

Just a couple days ago I put on some music, and a song came on that I noticed was from 2000. It then made me feel so unbelievably old and nostalgic in a sad way. Realizing I couldn‚Äôt get that moment in life back, but it seemed so much better than the present. I felt the goosebumps come all down my body, and I started to tear up. It‚Äôs such a small thing, but it really affected me.

I‚Äôm trying to remember some of the stories I‚Äôve heard since living here. There is one pretty famous story about a big battle between the monkeys and the giants (yeaksa). I saw it performed late last year at a place in Phnom Penh called Sovannaphum Arts Association. I believe the story is from an epic called Reamker.

I‚Äôve also heard of a couple little legends while living here. One of the first things I noticed was how stairs in houses often seem to be of different heights. Someone told me this is to keep spirits from being able to climb them. 

There‚Äôs also a belief that may come from Chinese myths about what to do if someone gets Mumps. You are supposed to find someone who was born in the year of the tiger. That person should circle your enlarged cheek with their fingernail. This will help heal you.

Finally, one of the most famous stories I‚Äôve encountered is Bpos Keng Kang (·ûñ·ûü·üã·ûÄ·üÅ·ûÑ·ûÄ·ûÑ). In this story, a lady falls in love with the snake king. He impregnates her and then her husband finds out. He kills the snake king and then his wife and all of the snake babies. One of them escapes and is supposed to be Naga, the famous snake you see in many statues here.

This has honestly helped me a lot. Plus doing some intermittent fasting to get back to a normal weight. I have a pretty bad addictive personality, so I have a hard time sticking to doing things in moderation: eating, drinking alcohol, being lazy, etc. I have messed around with meditation before, but being isolated at home has really gotten me back into it. 

I also think not eating for 18-20 hours a day and only eating in the remaining 4-6 hours has helped make me a lot more disciplined. I‚Äôm just more conscious of what I‚Äôm consuming in that short window of time. I suppose that concept could be applied to other things that people tend to indulge in... drinking, being lazy, etc. Maybe set a window of time each day where those things are allowed, then restrict them when outside of that window of time.
